3. 養聲
廣東話：個歌手最近聲帶發炎，醫生話佢要靜養，專心養聲先可以返工。
English: The singer's vocal cords are inflamed recently; the doctor said he needs to rest and focus on recovering his voice before he can work again.

4. 票尾
廣東話：你張戲飛嘅票尾仲有冇？要留返做收據先可以退錢。
English: Do you still have the stub of your movie ticket? You need to keep it as a receipt to get a refund.

5. hacker
廣東話：呢個 hacker 好叻，可以幾分鐘內就 hack 入政府嘅電腦系統。
English: This hacker is very skilled; he can hack into the government's computer system within a few minutes.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：阿爸好鍾意種石斛蘭，因為佢地係依附喺樹上面生長，好有特色。
English: Dad loves growing Dendrobium orchids because they grow attached to trees, which is very unique.

7. 吊詭
廣東話：佢話要節省開支，但係成日去高級餐廳食飯，真係好吊詭。
English: He says he wants to save money, but he goes to high-end restaurants all the time; it's really paradoxical.

8. 吊詭
廣東話：呢個情況好吊詭，明明係為咗大家好，結果反而搞到大家更唔開心。
English: This situation is quite absurd; it was meant to be for everyone's good, but in the end, it made everyone even unhappier.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：兩個公司嘅員工雖然以前係朋友，但而家各為其主，喺商戰入面都要對住打。
English: Although the employees of the two companies were friends before, now they each serve their own masters and have to fight against each other in business warfare.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：部車嘅軨蓋（即係呔軨）壞咗，要快啲去車房修返好先可以行。
English: The car's hood (bonnet) is broken; we need to go to the garage to fix it quickly before we can drive.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：阿叔退休之後，成日同班老友去球場打哥夫，好享受。
English: After retiring, Uncle often goes to the golf course to play golf with his old friends and enjoys it very much.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間店賣嘅蛋糕係免揀嘅，你買咗就係邊個都唔知係邊個，要睇手氣。
English: The cakes sold in this shop are "no choice" (random); once you buy one, you don't know which one you get, it's all about luck.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢成日擺闊佬，成日請人食最貴嘅飯，其實佢個荷包根本唔夠用。
English: He always tries to show off his wealth by treating people to the most expensive meals, even though his wallet can't actually afford it.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我細個好鍾意聽收音機入面嘅廣播劇，成日聽住佢地講故事瞓覺。
English: When I was young, I loved listening to radio dramas on the radio; I often fell asleep listening to their stories.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：以前我屋企有一部錄影機，成日用嚟錄電視節目返嚟睇。
English: My family used to have a video recorder, which we often used to record TV programs to watch later.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：佢偷咗公司嘅錢，證據吟詩吟唔甩，最後只可以認罪。
English: He stole money from the company; the evidence is irrefutable, so he had to confess in the end.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：下個禮拜日教會會舉辦一個大型佈道大會，歡迎大家去參加。
English: The church will hold a large evangelistic meeting next Sunday; everyone is welcome to attend.

18. 寫手
廣東話：佢係一個好有名嘅寫手，成日為雜誌寫專欄文章。
English: He is a very famous writer who often writes column articles for magazines.

19. 寫手
廣東話：呢個明星嘅自傳其實係請咗一個寫手代筆寫嘅，唔係佢自己寫。
English: This celebrity's autobiography was actually written by a ghostwriter, not by the celebrity themselves.

20. 代打
廣東話：我今日好忙，唔可以打機，你幫我做個代打先啦。
English: I'm very busy today and can't play games; can you be my proxy player for me?

21. 茶碗
廣東話：日本茶道入面，個茶碗嘅形狀同質感都好重要，係由陶瓷燒製而成。
English: In Japanese tea ceremony, the shape and texture of the tea bowl are very important; it is made of fired ceramics.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：沖茶嘅時候，記得用茶隔將茶葉同茶湯分開，咁樣飲落去先唔會塞牙。
English: When brewing tea, remember to use a tea strainer to separate the tea leaves from the tea soup, so it won't get stuck in your teeth when you drink it.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：老闆自己成日遲到早退，但係對員工就要求好嚴，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The boss is always late and leaves early, but demands strictness from employees; it's truly a case of "the magistrate is allowed to set fires, but the common people are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：今晚個演唱會，佢會喺最後一首歌進行獨唱，好期待。
English: At tonight's concert, she will perform a solo for the last song; I'm looking forward to it.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢係個快人快事嘅人，有嘢講就即刻講，唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He is a straightforward person; if he has something to say, he says it immediately without dragging things out.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：唔好喺公廁入面做四腳獸，好唔衛生又唔文明。
English: Don't engage in "four-legged beast" activities (intimacy) in the public restroom; it's unsanitary and uncivilized.

27. 無米粥
廣東話：呢個項目仲係煲無米粥嘅階段，好多細節都未定，大家先唔好期望太高。
English: This project is still in the "cooking rice without rice" stage; many details are not yet settled, so everyone shouldn't have high expectations yet.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前好多低下階層嘅人會參加義會，大家集資幫手，邊個急需用錢就標會拎錢。
English: In the past, many people from lower social classes would join a "Yi Hui" (rotating savings and credit association), pooling money together so that whoever needed money urgently could bid for the funds.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代官府有嘢要宣佈，就會喺城門口貼出榜文，俾百姓睇。
English: In ancient times, when the government wanted to announce something, they would post a notice (bangwen) at the city gate for the people to read.

30. MK 名
廣東話：佢喺網上個 MK 名好特別，前面加咗好多特殊符號，仲有「堅系」呢個字頭。
English: His online nickname (MK name) is very special; it has many special symbols at the front and starts with the word "Gin Sai" (meaning "definitely"). [end of text]


